speech.p:
That, for the purposes of any Act of the present Session to establish public authorities concerned with arrangements for persons to obtain employment, it is expedient to authorize—


(1) the payment out of moneys provided by Parliament of any expenses incurred by the Secretary of State for the purposes of that Act and any increase attributable to that Act in the sums payable out of such moneys under any other Act;

(2) the payment into the Consolidated Fund of any sums received by the Secretary of State by virtue of that Act.—[Mr. Dudley Smith.]
